FitTrack - Fitness Goal Tracker
FitTrack is a Blazor WebAssembly application designed to help users set, log, and track their fitness goals. 
This simple web app demonstrates core Blazor skills, including in-memory data management, form handling, and responsive design with Bootstrap.

Features
User Profile: Allows users to create and edit a basic profile with name and age.
Workout Logging: Users can log workouts with type and duration, and view a history of logged workouts.
Goal Setting and Progress Tracking: Users can set fitness goals (e.g., target distances) and update progress over time.
Responsive Design: Optimized layout using Bootstrap for a seamless experience on various devices.
Technologies Used
Frontend: Blazor WebAssembly, Bootstrap
Languages: C#, HTML, CSS
Data Management: In-memory storage within Blazor (no server-side dependencies)

Getting Started
Prerequisites
Visual Studio 2022 (or later) with the .NET 8 SDK installed.
Basic knowledge of Blazor WebAssembly and C#.
Installation
Clone the Repository:

bash

git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/FitTrack.git
cd FitTrack

Open in Visual Studio:

Open the solution file (.sln) in Visual Studio.
Run the Application:
In Visual Studio, set the project as the startup project.
Click Start Debugging or press F5 to launch the app locally.
Running Locally
Once the app is running, open your browser and go to http://localhost:5000 (or the URL specified in your output). 
You should see the main interface with options to:

Create or edit your profile
Log new workouts
Set and track goals
